# Scope

This rule is attached when editing **`apps/web`** (use `@innovate-test/env/web`) or **`packages/env`** (schema definitions for web and server). For server-only consumption patterns in `apps/server`, prefer aligning with the same env package rules when touching `packages/env`; server app code is not in this rule’s path.

# Environment variables (`@innovate-test/env`)

Typed env validation lives in the **`@innovate-test/env`** package with two separate entrypoints:

- **`@innovate-test/env/web`** — Vite-prefixed client-side vars (safe to expose to the browser).
- **`@innovate-test/env/server`** — Server-only vars (database URLs, secrets, etc.).

Both use `createEnv` from `@t3-oss/env-core` with Zod schemas.

## Consuming env in the web app (`apps/web`)

```ts
import { env } from "@innovate-test/env/web"

const apiUrl = env.VITE_SERVER_URL
```

## Consuming env in the server or packages (`apps/server`, `packages/*`)

```ts
import { env } from "@innovate-test/env/server"

const dbUrl = env.DATABASE_URL
```

## Rules

- **Never read `process.env` or `import.meta.env` directly** in feature or package code — always import from `@innovate-test/env/web` or `@innovate-test/env/server`.
- **Never import `@innovate-test/env/server`** from `apps/web` — it contains secrets.
- **Do not create a local `src/env.ts`** in `apps/web` or any package; the shared `@innovate-test/env` package is the single source of truth.
- To add a new env var, declare and validate it with a Zod schema in `packages/env/src/web.ts` (for Vite-prefixed vars) or `packages/env/src/server.ts` (for server-only vars).
- All required env vars must be declared in `createEnv`; prefer making them required and setting defaults in infra rather than using `z.optional()`.
